<i>noun</i>: 윤색 [윤ː색], 수식 [수식] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>윤색 [윤ː색]</dt><br>
<dd>embellishment</dd><br>
<dd>(비유적으로) 사실을 과장하거나 좋게 꾸밈.</dd><br>
<dd>(figurative) The state of exaggerating or beautifying an incident.</dd><br>
<dt>수식 [수식]</dt><br>
<dd>1. decoration</dd><br>
<dd>겉모양을 꾸밈.</dd><br>
<dd>An adornment of the appearance.</dd><br>
<dd>2. embellishment</dd><br>
<dd>글이나 문장의 표현을 화려하고 기교 있게 꾸밈.</dd><br>
<dd>An embellishment of the expression in a composition or sentence in a fanciful and stylish manner.</dd><br>
<dd>3. modification</dd><br>
<dd>문법에서, 관형어나 부사어 등을 체언이나 용언에 덧붙여 그 뜻을 분명하게 하거나 꾸미는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>A linguistic phenomenon in which an adnominal phrase, adverb, etc., relates to a substantive or a predicate in a sentence by way of specifying its meaning or qualifying it in other ways.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>